-- BP, Azerbaijan Approve Next Phase of Shah Deniz Gas Development
-- B y   Z u l f u g a r   A g a y e v
-- 2012-04-17T12:24:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/bp-azerbaijan-approve-next-phase-of-shah-deniz-gas-development.html
BP Plc (BP/) , leading  Azerbaijan ’s $25
billion Shah Deniz 2 gas project, approved the next phase of
development as the country studies export routes to  Europe .  BP Chief Executive Officer Bob Dudley and Azeri President
 Ilham Aliyev  approved the start of the so-called front-end
engineering and design process, BP’s local office in Baku said
today in an e-mailed statement. FEED comprises engineering
studies, wells, commercial agreements and construction deals.  Azerbaijan and the development partners at Shah Deniz are
evaluating proposed pipeline routes to Europe via  Turkey ,
including the European Union-backed Nabucco project, the Trans-
Adriatic Pipeline and BP’s South-East Europe Pipeline. The group
will make a decision in 2013 and start exports around the end of
2017, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zulfugar Agayev in Baku at 
